        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I'm KoS (got the hammer before I was KoS) and still use it frequently.  It drops you in the middle of the ship that the skeleton workers are constructing.  When you pop in KoS there is one skeleton that will agro on you and start attacking, he is green to me but still hits for 60+ on occasion.  I just make sure to have Root and Levant up when I zone into OT, then I just root the skeleton, step back, and Levant over to near the Warslik Woods zone.  </P><P>The first time I did it I tried rooting him, then ran out and FD to lose the agro, popped up and hit the CoS and thought I was fine... then I went to run through the gate and suddenly had a Dragoon and one of the Golems from the gate beating hard on me.  I never saw any message about getting hit before that, and didnt' think either of those saw thru invis, so I'm not sure what happened... maybe one of the other skels hit me and I didn't see it or something.  I think I finally got a FD off with about 30 hp left to lose the Goon and Golem.</P><P>So it can be dangerous if you're KoS and sloppy, but I do the root/levant method now and find it to be very little risk.</P><P></P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=235322" target="_blank">Zetapsi Kappaphi</a> - 59 Dark-elf Necromonster <BR>The Watchmen of Karana<BR><a href="http://www.betawatcher.com/" target="_blank">Betawatcher.com - Shape your world!</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
